Implementation driven by workshop requirements:
- Must work on student laptops with unknown configurations
- Network environments vary (corporate proxies, firewalls)
- Cloud environments have unique constraints (Replit, Codespaces)
- Students may have partial tool installations

Design decisions:
- Visual feedback with emojis for quick scanning
- Platform-specific fix commands reduce friction
- JSON report helps instructors debug remotely
- Non-fatal warnings for optional components

Testing approach:
- Manually tested on macOS ARM64, Linux x64, WSL2
- Simulated missing tools by PATH manipulation
- Verified fix commands on each platform
